<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>7.3 Liter Diesel Engine Service (1991) - CRANKSHAFT, MAIN BEARINGS, FLYWHEEL AND CRANKCASE - OIL LEVEL GAUGE
        TUBE (Removal and Reassembly)
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>OIL LEVEL GAUGE TUBE (Removal and Reassembly)</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="0">
            <title>REMOVAL</title>
            <para>Remove the oil level gauge as follows, refer to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk document="e435_121.xml" xrefid="ef4350639">6.39</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the 5/16 in. nut and washer which secures the upper oil level gauge tube with
                    bracket, at the exhaust manifold.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the upper oil level gauge tube assembly from the crankcase at the lower tube.
                    Remove the sealing O-ring and discard.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
